Remove upsidedown package import from bleve/v2 top-level.

Bleve unconditionally imports index/upsidedown just for the Name constant.
That package contains protobuf-generated code (upsidedown.pb.go) whose init()
triggers reflect.Type.Method() calls that defeat the Go linker's dead-code
elimination when combined with openai-go's reflect.Type embedding.

This patch replaces upsidedown.Name with the string literal "upside_down"
in the 3 affected files, eliminating the protobuf dependency chain.

See pkg/rag/README.md section 19 for full analysis.

--- a/vendor/github.com/blevesearch/bleve/v2/index.go
+++ b/vendor/github.com/blevesearch/bleve/v2/index.go
@@ -18,7 +18,6 @@
 	"context"
 	"fmt"
 
-	"github.com/blevesearch/bleve/v2/index/upsidedown"
 
 	"github.com/blevesearch/bleve/v2/document"
 	"github.com/blevesearch/bleve/v2/mapping"
@@ -298,7 +297,7 @@
